parameters.name: AccountName
parameters.description:
The sender address.

> Leave this parameter empty to query all addresses. If TagName is specified, this parameter is required.

parameters.name: DedicatedIp
parameters.description:
The dedicated IP address to query. This parameter is for users of dedicated IPs.

If this parameter is not specified, data for all dedicated IPs is queried.

parameters.name: DedicatedIpPoolId
parameters.description:
The ID of the dedicated IP pool to query. This parameter is for users of dedicated IPs.

If this parameter is not specified, data for all IP pools is queried.

parameters.name: EndTime
parameters.description: The end time. The time range between the start and end times cannot exceed 7 days. The format is yyyy-MM-dd.

parameters.name: Esp
parameters.description:
The Email Service Provider (ESP). This parameter is for users of dedicated IPs and queries data for a specific ESP. Valid values include the following:

- gmail.com

- yahoo.com

- outlook.com

- icloud.com

- others (for data from ESPs other than the ones listed)

If this parameter is not specified, data for all ESPs is queried.

parameters.name: Offset
parameters.description: The value is 0 for the first query and 1 for subsequent queries. A value of 1 indicates a paged query in chronological order. (This field is deprecated.)

parameters.name: OffsetCreateTime
parameters.description: Used for paging. Do not set this parameter for the first query. For subsequent queries, set it to the OffsetCreateTime value from the previous response. (This field is deprecated.)

parameters.name: PageSize
parameters.description: The number of entries per page.

parameters.name: StartTime
parameters.description: The start time. The time cannot be more than 30 days in the past. The format is yyyy-MM-dd.
